Voiceover-only channels — no face camera: AI voices narrate scripts while visuals play (slides, stock footage, generated images).
2) Tools you’ll likely use
Script writing / idea generation: ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, other LLMs.
Text-to-speech: ElevenLabs, Replica, Murf — for high-quality narration.
Image generation: Midjourney, Stable Diffusion, DALL•E, or open-source variants.
Video editing: CapCut, DaVinci Resolve (free), Premiere Pro.
Stock footage & music: Pexels, Pixabay, Storyblocks, Epidemic Sound (paid) or YouTube Audio Library (free).
Automation & workflow: Zapier, Make (Integromat), or Python scripts for batch generation.
3) Practical video formats & lengths
Shorts (15–60s): Quick tips, AI-generated art reveals, a single idea — fast growth potential.
Long-form (6–15+ minutes): Deep dives, tutorials, and listicles — better for watch time and monetization.
Series format: “AI Story of the Week”, “AI Prompt Battles”, or “Weekly AI News” — consistency helps channel growth.
4) Simple workflow (repeatable)
Idea/keyword research: Use YouTube search suggestions, TubeBuddy, or VidIQ.
Prompt the AI to produce a script or outline.
Edit script manually for clarity and voice.
Generate visuals (images, clips) and narration (TTS) or record your voice.
Edit video, add captions and background music.
Create thumbnail and SEO-optimized title/description/tags.
Publish and promote (shorts, community, social media).
5) SEO & growth tips
Titles: Clear, benefit-driven, include primary keyword.
Thumbnails: High contrast, readable text, one focal face/object.
Hook in first 5–10 seconds: Promise value fast.
Use chapters in longer videos and pinned comments to highlight resources.
Post consistently (1–3 times weekly to start) and analyze retention metrics.
Reuse content: Clip highlights into shorts; turn long videos into smaller segments.
6) Legal & ethical considerations
Don’t claim human authorship if misleading — be transparent about AI use when relevant.
Check copyright for any generated assets (music, images). Use licensed or royalty-free resources.
Avoid creating content that harms people (deepfakes, harassment, misinformation).
7) Monetization pathways
YouTube Partner Program (ads) once eligible.
Affiliate links, sponsorships, Patreon, channel memberships.
Sell courses or prompt packs, offer consulting or freelance prompt-writing.
